  "issue_number": 212,
  "issue_title": "Bug: ScreenSignalsExtractor over-counts clickable nodes from attribute text",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n`ScreenSignalsExtractor` over-counts clickable nodes: it counts a node as clickable whenever the substring `\" clickable\"` appears anywhere in the node line \u2014 including inside quoted attribute **values** like `text=\"Not clickable yet\"`.\n\n### Where\n`app/src/main/java/dev/touchpilot/app/screen/ocr/ScreenSignalsExtractor.kt:52`:\n```kotlin\nif (\" clickable\" in \" $body\") clickable += 1\n```\n`body` is the full per-line node body, including quoted `text=\"...\"`/`desc=\"...\"` values (real dump format from `TouchPilotAccessibilityService.appendNode`).\n\n### Root cause\nThe dump emits both attribute values and the bare flag token ` clickable`. The clickable detector scans the whole body, so a non-clickable node whose label contains the word \u2014 e.g. `- TextView node_id=\"0\" text=\"Not clickable yet\"` \u2014 matches and is counted. The two sibling extractors on the same node are correctly scoped (`TEXT_ATTR`/`DESC_ATTR` use anchored regexes; the input-field check uses `CLASS_NAME.find(body)` on the leading class token only). The clickable check is the lone one inspecting attribute values.\n\n### Why it's a real bug (not intended)\n`ScreenSignalsExtractorTest` exercises clickable counting only with the bare ` clickable` token and never feeds a label containing the word, so no test pins this false-positive path; the inconsistency with the correctly-scoped sibling extractors confirms it's unintended.\n\n### Impact\nInflated `clickableNodeCount` feeds `ContextQualityDetector.classify`. A genuinely weak screen (no real affordances, just text mentioning \"clickable\") can be misclassified as `Strong`, suppressing the OCR/weak-context fallback the detector is documented to bias toward \u2014 so the agent guesses from insufficient data instead of degrading honestly.\n\n### Fix\nStrip quoted attribute values before scanning for the bare `clickable` flag token. Regression test included. PR attached.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-10T14:10:01.000Z",
